To create HTML website. We need to name the file as index.html 
We type html and automatically we get a structure. In the structure we change add to the body.
The body we divide it by divs and to create a line bigger we add the h1 
You can have divs inside other divs. 
<h1>ALUVIYER: Taller de Aluminio y Vidrio</h1> para hacerlo mas grande 



<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

    <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My website</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
    </head>
    <body>
        <div id="container">
            <div id="header">
                <div id="my logo">ALUVIYER</div>
                <div>Taller de aluminio y vidrio</div>
            </div>
            <div id="panel">VENTANAS</div>

            <div id="panel2">PUERTAS</div>
            <main id="body">VITRINAS </main>
            <div id="footer">PASAMANOS</div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>


!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

    <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My website</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
    </head>
    <body>
        <div id="container">
            <div id="col1">col1</div>
            <div id="col2">col2</div>
        </div>
        <div id="col3">col3</div>
    </body>
</html>

For style.css 

#container{
    background-color: rgb(0, 247, 255);

}

#col1{
    background-color: aquamarine;
    width: 30%;
}

#col2{
    background-color: blueviolet;
    width:40%;


}
#col3{

    background-color: brown;
    width:50%;
}


/*   */

To use flex

on the style css we say 

#container {

    display:flex;
    justify-content: space-between; 
    width: 80%;
    margin:0 auto;

    }

#container {

    /*By default Flex makes the items go next by each other */

    display:flex;
    justify-content: space-between; 
    width: 80%;
    margin:0 auto;

    }

#Trending {

    display:flex;
    flex-direction:column;
    gap: 10px;



}  



